attacks.name: Euphoria GX
attacks.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Asleep. Heal all damage from all of your Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

attacks.name: Sonic Edge
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

abilities.name: Dragon Lift
abilities.text: Your Pokémon in play have no Retreat Cost, except Pokémon-GX and Pokémon-EX.

attacks.name: Flame Jet GX
attacks.text: This attack does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) (You can’t use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

attacks.name: Bright Flame
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Shred
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Raging Blade
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any damage counters on it, this attack does 80 more damage.

attacks.name: Dragon Nova GX
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned and Paralyzed. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

340262987.name: Dragon Talon
340262987.text: If the {N} Pokémon this card is attached to is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if that Pokémon is Knocked Out), put 3 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

340262988.name: Fiery Flint
340262988.text:
You can play this card only if you discard 2 other cards from your hand.

Search your deck for up to 4 {R} Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

340262989.name: Switch Raft
340262989.text: Switch your Active {W} Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If you do, heal 30 damage from the Pokémon you moved to your Bench.

attacks.name: Photon Geyser
attacks.text: Discard all basic {P} Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 80 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

attacks.name: Sky-Scorching Light GX
attacks.text: You can use this attack only if the total of both players’ remaining Prize cards is 6 or less. Put 6 damage counters on each of your opponent’s Pokémon. (You can’t use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

340319233.name: Dragon Majesty
340319233.description: Noble Pokémon of wing and claw, flying high above the changing world! The Pokémon TCG: Dragon Majesty expansion brings a mighty horde of draconic Pokémon: Reshiram-GX, Salamence-GX, Dragonite-GX, and over a dozen more, including Charizard! Their command of fire, battle, and sky puts Dragon types at the top of many Trainers’ lists—get to know these amazing and challenging Pokémon in the Dragon Majesty expansion!
